public void setLabelProvider(IBaseLabelProvider labelProvider) {
	IBaseLabelProvider oldProvider = this.labelProvider;
	if (oldProvider != null) {
		oldProvider.removeListener(this.labelProviderListener);
	}
	this.labelProvider = labelProvider;
	if (labelProvider != null) {
		labelProvider.addListener(this.labelProviderListener);
	}
	refresh();

	// Dispose old provider after refresh, so that items never refer to 
stale images.
	if (oldProvider != null) {
****		oldProvider.dispose();
	}
}

Bug.WithStack:
When an error occurs in the init of a text editor, the status of the 
CoreException is thrown away. This may contain information that is useful which 
should be displayed to the user.

In this method is the following code: 

  try {
    doSetInput(input);
  } catch (CoreException x) {
    throw new PartInitException(x.getMessage());
  }
A better version would be:

  try {
    doSetInput(input);
  } catch (CoreException x) {
    throw new PartInitException(x.getStatus());
  }

as this would pass all the information to the caller
Build 20020430.

